The Duchy of Normandy was ruled by dukes including:  
- Rollo, the Viking leader who established the duchy through the Treaty of Saint-Clair-sur-Epte with King Charles III of West Francia in 911;  
- Richard I of Normandy, who forged it into a cohesive and formidable principality;  
- Richard II of Normandy;  
- William II of Normandy (William the Conqueror), who conquered England in 1066.  

Additionally, early Norman kings of England (as Dukes of Normandy) owed homage to the King of France for their continental lands.
